      <hedline>
        <hl1>Rethink Missile Defense</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Eric Gidal letter on 'foolishness and danger' of proposed missile defense system (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Study Said to Find U.S. Missile Shield Might Incite China'' (front page, Aug. 10): Nothing exposes the poverty of our current political dialogue more than the discussion of national missile defense.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Study Said to Find U.S. Missile Shield Might Incite China'' (front page, Aug. 10): Nothing exposes the poverty of our current political dialogue more than the discussion of national missile defense.</p>
        <p>Despite abundant evidence of the foolishness and danger of deploying a system that will waste vast domestic resources and destabilize global relations, the American voting public is given the choice between a candidate who embraces its land deployment and a candidate who wants to expand it to sea and space. Will no national leader speak up for sanity and restraint?</p>
        <p>ERIC GIDAL  Iowa City, Aug. 10, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
